{"id":14881471,"mediaExerciseId":"4039841d-1613-4ddd-b616-a2b77ea6d082","exerciseName":"19","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":491,"solutions":[{"id":5986627,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, we have to find out the weighted average of floating cost which we denote with $WF$, where the  weight of debt $WD$ is $25\\%$, floating of debt $FD$ is $2\\%$, the weight of equity $WE$ is $70\\%$, floating of equity $FE$ is $7\\%$, the weight of preferred stock $WP$ is $5\\%$ and the floating preferred stock $FP$ is $4\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nWF&=(WD \\times FD) + (WE \\times FE) + (WP \\times FP)\\\\[7pt]\n&=(25\\% \\times 2\\%)+(70\\% \\times 7\\%)+(5\\% \\times 4\\%)\\\\[7pt]\n&=(0.25 \\times 0.02)+(0.7 \\times 0.07)+(0.05 \\times 0.04)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.005+0.049+0.002\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.056\\\\[7pt]\n&=5.6\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nSo, the weighted average of floating cost is $\\boxed{5.6\\%}$\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let's find out the actual initial cost which we denote with $AC$, where the weighted average of floating cost $WF$ is $5.6\\%$ and the new project money $NM$ is $\\$80,000,000$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nAC &=\\frac{NM}{1-WF}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{80,000,000}{1-5.6\\%}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{80,000,000}{1-0.056}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{80,000,000}{0.944}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\$84,745,762.71\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the actual initial cost is $\\boxed{\\$84,745,762.71}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":" $\\boxed{\\$84,745,762.71}$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":48,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/471b4b3f889cb81ab9579c3fc2c4085b/9e923e0577f1394d54fe68a00b4af152/lateximg_large.png","width":222},"regular":{"height":24,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/471b4b3f889cb81ab9579c3fc2c4085b/9e923e0577f1394d54fe68a00b4af152/lateximg.png","width":111}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"429fcd4b-4111-454e-8151-59b7727daf3d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881472,"exerciseName":"20","page":491,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7992d82c-e286-49ae-bf7b-24857e2e81b5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-questions-and-problems-20-7992d82c-e286-49ae-bf7b-24857e2e81b5"},{"id":14881473,"exerciseName":"21","page":491,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7447979d-7181-4b1a-98e1-10e618beaa61","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-questions-and-problems-21-7447979d-7181-4b1a-98e1-10e618beaa61"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881470,"exerciseName":"18","page":490,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7322ff2a-e25d-47cb-8ac3-623dfcb659f3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundament